# agent-ssh Project Rules

## Build commands
- `just check` — fast Rust compile check
- `just lint` — format + clippy (CI gate, must pass)
- `just mac-build` — full macOS signed build
- `just mac-build-dev` — debug build with development signing
- `just mac-test` — Swift framework + FFI integration tests
- `just mac-bindings` — regenerate FFI bindings after editing `src/ffi.rs`

## Architecture
- macOS UI: `AgentSshApp/` — SwiftUI + AppKit
- iPadOS UI: `AgentSshMobile/`
- Shared framework: `Sources/AgentSshMacOS/`
- Rust FFI surface: `src/ffi.rs` (uniffi exports)
- Generated bindings: `bindings/midnight_ssh.swift`
- Xcode project generated from `project.yml` — never hand-edit `.xcodeproj`

## Swift conventions
- `BridgeManager` is the single FFI entry point — extensions: `BridgeManager+<Feature>.swift`
- `@MainActor` on all UI-mutating code
- State classes use `*Store` / `*Manager` naming

## Rust/FFI conventions
- FFI functions exported via `#[uniffi::export]` in `src/ffi.rs`
- Error returns at FFI boundary: `Result<T, String>`
- Any network call: `RUNTIME.block_on(async { … })`

## Critical rules
- NEVER manually edit `bindings/midnight_ssh.swift` — FFI checksum mismatch causes crash at `rshellInit()`
- After any FFI change: `just mac-bindings` + commit generated bindings
- Stale SPM cache fix: `rm -rf build .build && just mac-gen && just mac-build`
